Did the participant die during a consented study phase? Death was adjudicated for CT and OS participants through Ext1. This variable censors deaths that occur after the participant's last consented study phase, e.g. if a participant did not consent to Ext 1, but we discovered that she died during Ext1, DEATH would have a value of 0. This is done because the discovery rate of death is inconsistent after participant followup ends. See the DEATHSRC variable for details about the death adjudication process.
